  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 04:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] V5 Strategy Optimization: min_bias Filter + HL Consolidation Math\n\n**Task:** Analyze all V3+ trade data (78 trades, Mar 25-30) to find the highest-EV parameter changes for V5, and quantify the HL\u2192PM consolidation case.\n\n**Finding \u2014 Bias Sweet Spot is CLEAR:**\n- |bias| 45-60: **70% WR** (44 trades) \u2014 our bread and butter\n- |bias| 30-45: **46% WR** (26 trades) \u2014 actively LOSING money\n- |bias| <30: 62% WR (8 trades) \u2014 too small to trust\n\nWithin V4.1 hours only, it's even sharper:\n- |bias| 45-60 + V4.1 hours: **85% WR** (20 trades, 17W/3L)\n- |bias| 45-60 + entry \u2265$0.50: **100% WR** (11W/0L) \u2190 undefeated\n- |bias| 30-45 + V4.1 hours: 67% WR (9 trades) \u2014 acceptable but weaker\n\n**Finding \u2014 V4.1 Hour Filter is Massive Edge:**\n- V4.1 hours [11,12,19,20]: **77.1% WR** (27W/8L)\n- Non-V4.1 hours: **48.8% WR** (21W/22L) \u2014 coin flip\n- Delta: **+28.3pp** from hour selection alone\n\n**Finding \u2014 HL Consolidation is a No-Brainer:**\n- PM generates ~3.26%/day on capital (V4.1 projected)\n- HL generates ~0.11%/day on capital (slow bleed with occasional gains)\n- PM is **30x more capital-efficient** than HL right now\n- Moving $365 HL \u2192 PM would add ~$13/day to projected revenue\n- Consolidated $1,327 \u2192 $43/day projected (vs $30/day current)\n- Monthly impact: +$290/month from consolidation alone\n\n**My Thinking:**\nThe data strongly argues for TWO V5 changes:\n1. **Raise min_bias to 45** \u2014 eliminates the 30-45 bucket that's losing money. Cuts trade count from ~5 to ~3/day in V4.1 hours but raises EV/trade from 0.23x to 0.40x. Net daily EV improves 1.2x.\n2. **Consolidate HL to PM** \u2014 the capital efficiency gap is enormous. HL positions are barely moving ($2.84 uPnL on $365 over days). Same capital in PM = $13/day more.\n\nThe **bias \u226545 + entry \u2265$0.50 + V4.1 hours** combo is 100% WR (11/11). Small sample but the pattern is clear: when the market confirms the contrarian signal (entry above 0.50 = market is pricing the other side), AND bias is strong enough (\u226545), we win every time.\n\nMax consecutive losses in V4.1 hours: 2. Current stop-loss of 2 losses/hour is perfect \u2014 we never hit 3.\n\n**Decision:**\n- V5 min_bias=45 goes into the patch queue. Will backtest the Mar 25 data with this filter to confirm projected improvement before deploying.\n- HL consolidation: recommend to Hani. Close BTC LONG + SOL LONG on HL old wallet, withdraw $365 + $37 from both wallets, deposit to PM proxy.\n- NOT deploying today \u2014 V4.1 needs 1 full week of stability (deployed Mar 30, review Mar 37).\n- Will write the V5 backtest script next P3 heartbeat.\n\n**Next P3:** Build v5-min-bias-backtest.py \u2014 replay all 78 V3+ trades through proposed V5 filters (min_bias=45) and compare projected P&L against actual.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-30 19:25 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Correlation + Monday Trade Review\n\n**Task:** Correlate Fear & Greed with WR. Review first Monday with new filters.\n\n**Findings:**\n1. ",
